text: Rotta: It’s good to be home!

Osseus: It has a…
Charm all its own.
Rotta: You don’t even HAVE a nose.
Osseus: I know. That’s how strong the odor is.
Gobkin: Is kinda stinky…

Rotta: My father, the stub-tailed, short-toothed, son of a bilge rat, rules this section of the dungeon.
If you want my people’s cooperation… you’ll have to kill him.
Gobkin: Da feets, not kills.
Rotta: A sword through the heart will be the only thing he understands.
Osseus: We shall cross that sewer grate when we reach it, for now let’s hasten.
Rat Guard 1: By the chewstick of my ancestors, this stuff is so heavy.
RatGuard 2: My paws are killing me. And this helmet, why the horns? I’m constantly bumping them on the ceiling.

Rotta: I keep telling you to take it off!
We’re not meant to wear armor like that!
Rat Guard 1: Rotta!? You’re not supposed to be here!
Rotta: I need to speak to my father, step aside.

Rat Guard 1: Sorry, no can do. We got our orders.
For King Verpfeifen!
Osseus: Are you the only one of your kind to master the art of walking upright?

Rotta: No, it’s the armor. My mother was a grey rat, huge, and her clan wore this kind of armor.
But when she died, the grey rats abandoned us, and so my father made my clan wear their armor,
thinking it was the only way to protect them without the Grey’s strength
Gobkin: Vhat would you dos insteads?

Rotta: Though I hate to admit it, we are… Adorable.
I told my father we should use that to our advantage.
Lure enemies to their deaths with our cuteness, and when they lowered their guard…
pounce!
Osseus: You know… that’s actually kind of brilliant.
Gobkin: What Da say?
Rotta: Nothing of consequence.
Rotta: I don’t know if I can do it.
Osseus: Do what?
Rotta: Kill my dad.
Gobkin: Then don’t kills! We talks!

Rotta: He won’t listen.
He never listened.

Verpfeifen: I AM VERPFEIFEN! KING OF THE RATS! WHO DARES ENTER MY DOMAIN!
I AM THE BRINGER OF PLAGUES, THE CHEWER OF WALLS, AND THE BANE OF CHEESES!
Rotta: Dad, it’s me, Rotta!
Verpfeifen: What?! I can’t see anything in this helmet!
Verpfeifen: Rotta!? What are you doing here? I ordered you to leave and never return!
Rotta: And I hate to disobey, but adventurers are coming! We need the rat clan to stand with us or we’ll all die!
Verpfeifen: We shall face them alone! Let them crash and shatter upon our armor like waves upon rocks!

Rotta: We can’t wear armor like this, I keep telling you! They’ll knock us over and we’ll be turtles on our backs!
If we've reached the throne room, those adventurers will too!

Verpfeifen: If they do, then I shall unleash my own strength… like I’m afraid I must do now.
BRING ME MY ARMOR!
Rat Armorer: HNNNGGGGGGHHHH!
Verpfeifen: Now you will know the power of the King of the Rats, for in my might armor I will -
Rat Armorer: NGGGHHHH! BRING THE BREASTPLATE STRETCHER!
Verpfiefen: Would you hurry it up!?
Verpfeifen: Ahem - For in my mighty armor, I AM UNASSAILABLE!
Rotta: Why don’t you ever listen!
Verpfeifen: Because you’re a fool! You’re too young to know what responsibility this crown brings!
Rotta: I know that you’re leading us all to our doom!
Verpfeifen: Your mother crafted this armor, it is all I have of her!
Rotta: YOU HAVE ME!
Verpfeifen: And I can’t lose YOU! I WON’T! If I have to clad this entire dungeon in armor to protect you, I will!
Verpfeifen: You truly are your mother’s daughter.
Rotta: Then why did you send me away?

Verpfeifen: I have asked myself that every day since you left.
I wanted to keep you safe, and when you refused to wear the armor I…
I couldn’t bear the thought of what might happen. So I drove you away…
Because I was afraid to lose you… It all seems so ridiculous now.
Rotta: You could never lose me, father. I’m your daughter too, not just mom’s.
Verpfeifen: So… you really think your plan will work? Get rid of our armor and… play cute?
Rotta: It’ll work. I promise you.

Verpfeifen: Well then, you heard her everyone. Let’s throw this armor out.
Oh this is going to do wonders for my lower back!
